article.headline: W. Illinois 19, Indiana St. 7
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- Herb Donaldson rushed for 191 yards and a touchdown to lead Western Illinois to a 19-7 victory over Indiana State on Saturday. The Leathernecks (4-2, 1-0 Gateway Football Conference) had a 6-0 lead on two Taylor Rowan field goals when Donaldson scored on a 5-yard run in the third quarter to complete a 15-play, 92-yard drive. Indiana State (0-6, 0-2) responded with a 3-yard touchdown pass by Reilly Murphy to Brian Jackson midway through the fourth quarter, but Western Illinois quarterback Matt Barr later scored on a nine-yard run. Western Illinois rushed for 338 yards on 71 carries, totaling 424 yards in offense to 264 for Indiana State. It was the 11th career 100-yard rushing game for Donaldson and his fourth of the season. Alex Douglas added 95 yards rushing on 24 carries for the Leathernecks.
